<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Standard diagnostic sequence</p>
    <h2>How we work through a fryer-not-heating call.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Symptom confirmation.</strong> Won't heat at all (cold start), won't reach setpoint (slow recovery), or shuts off mid-cycle (hi-limit trip pattern).</li>
      <li><strong>Hi-limit reset attempt and root-cause check.</strong> Reset, look for why it tripped (oil level, blocked air intake, thermostat behavior).</li>
      <li><strong>Pilot test (gas) or element continuity (electric).</strong> Visual on pilot stability, multimeter on element resistance.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermopile millivolt test (gas, standing pilot).</strong> 200-250 mV minimum at the gas valve terminal.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas pressure test at the valve outlet.</strong> Manometer reading; confirms valve regulation.</li>
      <li><strong>Burner inspection.</strong> Visual flame quality, orifice cleanliness.</li>
      <li><strong>Brand-specific error code read (Frymaster RE, FilterQuick, newer Pitco).</strong> Saves 30-45 minutes on units with diagnostic codes.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>We document each step with the customer so the diagnostic path from symptom to recommended repair is clear before any parts are ordered.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
